Title: Linking forum posts -compilers-02-T1.1
Description: The workers will be presented with posts from a forum thread where instructors of a course have replied to student posts. The worker is required to: identify the student post(s) that the instructor’s reply addresses. Instructor's reply post is highlighted
Keywords: tagging, categorization, discussion forum, forum threads, mooc
Input.posts:
I just started my final. In the start page it says: You may only take this exam once. You will have 4 hours from when you click the 'Start Quiz Now' button to submit your answers. The final exam is due Sunday before midnight. Any exam started by this time will receive full credit. Exams started after this time will receive NO credit. Make sure to do the appropriate math if you are in a different time zone. This made me think i have 4 hours for the final. But in the final itself it says: Warning: You have 29 minutes and 40 seconds to complete this quiz. So whats correct? :-(
Upvotes:
3
Well it says 'Any exam started by this time will receive full credit.' so i hope that's true :-) I just submitted and got this: 'You submitted this quiz on Mon 26 May 2014 12:46 AM PDT . You got a score of 9.75 out of 10.00 . However, you will not get credit for it, since it was submitted past the deadline.'
Upvotes:
3
Hello I had a similar issue, and created a thread about it. Have you reached a conclusion regarding this? In fact, my situation is worse because when the time expired, I was prompted to submit the exam, and I accepted. So I received only two points. I would like to be able to finish the course. Is there anything that can be done?
Upvotes:
2
Input.inst_post:
Instructor's Post
Hi students, The adjustment has been made and your score is now correct (without penalties). Best,
